      • initializeHistogram

        public static double[] initializeHistogram(float start,
                                           float end,
                                           float focusRangeStart,
                                           float focusRangeEnd,
                                           float errorPct)
        Generates an array of bucket lower bounds from start to end with a fixed error interval (i.e. the span of the buckets). Up to 100 buckets can be created using this method. Additionally, a range of measurements can be provided to "focus" on with a smaller bucket span while the remaining buckets have a wider span.
        Parameters:
        start - The starting bucket measurement (lower bound).
        end - The ending bucket measurement (upper bound).
        focusRangeStart - The focus range start bound. Can be the same as start.
        focusRangeEnd - The focus rang end bound. Can be the same as end.
        errorPct - The acceptable error with respect to bucket width. E.g. 0.05 for 5%.
        Returns:
        An array of bucket lower bounds.
